{"comments":"CVD - Color Vision Deficiency simulation and accessibility.\n\nColor blindness affects approximately 8% of males and 0.5% of females.\nDesigns must be accessible to people with all types of color vision.\n\n## Types of CVD\n\n**Red-Green Deficiencies (most common):**\n- **Protanopia**: No red cones (~1% males) - red appears dark\n- **Protanomaly**: Weak red cones (~1% males) - red shifted toward green\n- **Deuteranopia**: No green cones (~1% males) - green appears beige\n- **Deuteranomaly**: Weak green cones (~5% males) - green shifted toward red\n\n**Blue-Yellow Deficiencies (rare):**\n- **Tritanopia**: No blue cones (~0.001%) - blue appears green, yellow appears pink\n- **Tritanomaly**: Weak blue cones - blue/yellow confusion\n\n**Total Color Blindness (very rare):**\n- **Achromatopsia**: No color vision - sees only grayscale\n\n## Playground Integration\n\nThe showcase accessibility panel shows:\n- \"Normal Vision\" (original colors)\n- \"Protanopia\" (no red)\n- \"Deuteranopia\" (no green)\n- \"Tritanopia\" (no blue)\n- \"Achromatopsia\" (grayscale)\n\nFor each view, show contrast ratios and distinguishability warnings.\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[83,11],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[83,3]},"title":"Normal"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[84,15],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[84,3]},"title":"Protanopia"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[85,16],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[85,3]},"title":"Protanomaly"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[86,17],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[86,3]},"title":"Deuteranopia"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[87,18],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[87,3]},"title":"Deuteranomaly"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[88,15],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[88,3]},"title":"Tritanopia"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[89,16],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[89,3]},"title":"Tritanomaly"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[90,18],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[90,3]},"title":"Achromatopsia"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","CVD"],"CVDType"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[92,40],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[92,1]},"title":"eqCVDType"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","CVD"],"CVDType"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[93,42],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[93,1]},"title":"ordCVDType"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","CVD"],"CVDType"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[104,49],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[95,1]},"title":"showCVDType"}],"comments":"Types of color vision deficiency\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"data","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[90,18],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[82,1]},"title":"CVDType"},{"children":[],"comments":"Prevalence data for CVD types\n\nReturns percentage of population affected, separated by sex.\n\n**Sources (as of 2026-02-21):**\n- National Eye Institute (NEI): 1 in 12 men (8.33%), 1 in 200 women (0.5%)\n- Colour Blind Awareness (UK): Detailed breakdown by type\n\n**Total CVD prevalence: 8% males, 0.5% females worldwide**\n(Higher in Scandinavia: 10-11% males; Lower in sub-Saharan Africa)\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","CVD"],"CVDType"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["males",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["females",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[116,67],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[116,1]},"title":"cvdPrevalence"},{"children":[],"comments":"Single accessibility issue for one CVD type\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["cvdType",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","CVD"],"CVDType"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["actualContrast",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["requiredContrast",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["prevalenceMales",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["prevalenceFemales",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["message",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[142,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[135,1]},"title":"AccessibilityIssue"},{"children":[],"comments":"Complete accessibility report for all CVD types\n\nEither all CVD types pass (Right Unit), or we have a list of all failures.\nThe list is never empty if Left - at least one CVD type must fail.\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Either"],"Either"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Array"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","CVD"],"AccessibilityIssue"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},"tag":"ParensInType"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Unit"],"Unit"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[148,66],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[148,1]},"title":"AccessibilityReport"},{"children":[],"comments":"Simulate how a color appears with a given CVD type\n\nUses transformation matrices based on Brettel, Viénot and Mollon (1997)\nand Viénot, Brettel and Mollon (1999) research.\n\n```purescript\nsimulateCVD Deuteranopia (RGB.rgb 255 0 0)  -- How red looks with no green cones\nsimulateCVD Achromatopsia (RGB.rgb 59 130 246)  -- Blue becomes gray\n```\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","CVD"],"CVDType"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","RGB"],"RGB"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","RGB"],"RGB"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[163,45],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[163,1]},"title":"simulateCVD"},{"children":[],"comments":"Check if two colors are distinguishable for a given CVD type\n\nReturns true if the colors have sufficient contrast after CVD simulation.\nUses WCAG AA threshold (4.5:1) as minimum distinguishability.\n\n```purescript\nisDistinguishable Deuteranopia red green  -- Can these be told apart?\n```\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","CVD"],"CVDType"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","RGB"],"RGB"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","RGB"],"RGB"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Boolean"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[186,62],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[186,1]},"title":"isDistinguishable"},{"children":[],"comments":"Check accessibility for all CVD types and return all failures\n\nReturns Right unit if accessible for all CVD types, or Left with an array\nof ALL failures. The array is never empty if Left.\n\nFor showcase use: display all accessibility issues simultaneously so users\nunderstand the full impact of their color choices.\n\n```purescript\ncheckAccessibility red green\n-- Right unit  (all CVD types can distinguish these colors)\n-- OR\n-- Left [ { cvdType: Protanopia, actualContrast: 2.1, prevalenceMales: 1.0, ... }\n       , { cvdType: Deuteranopia, actualContrast: 1.8, prevalenceMales: 1.0, ... } ]\n```\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","RGB"],"RGB"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","RGB"],"RGB"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","CVD"],"AccessibilityReport"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[209,64],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[209,1]},"title":"checkAccessibility"},{"children":[],"comments":"Suggest an accessible alternative color\n\nGiven a foreground and background, suggest a foreground that works for\nall CVD types. Returns Nothing if the original is already accessible.\n\n```purescript\nsuggestAccessibleAlternative red green  -- Suggest better foreground\n```\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","RGB"],"RGB"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","RGB"],"RGB"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Maybe"],"Maybe"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","RGB"],"RGB"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[263,68],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[263,1]},"title":"suggestAccessibleAlternative"},{"children":[],"comments":"Ensure a color is accessible, correcting it if necessary\n\nFor showcase/playground use: automatically correct colors as users pick them.\nIf colors are already accessible, returns the original foreground unchanged.\nIf not accessible, returns a corrected version that works for all CVD types.\n\n```purescript\nensureAccessible red green  -- Returns red if accessible, corrected version if not\n```\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","RGB"],"RGB"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","RGB"],"RGB"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","RGB"],"RGB"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[288,50],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[288,1]},"title":"ensureAccessible"},{"children":[],"comments":"Check contrast for all CVD types\n\nReturns the minimum contrast ratio across all CVD simulations.\nUseful for ensuring designs work for everyone.\n\n```purescript\ncvdSafeContrast foreground background  -- Minimum contrast across all CVDs\n```\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","RGB"],"RGB"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","RGB"],"RGB"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[299,48],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/CVD.purs","start":[299,1]},"title":"cvdSafeContrast"}],"name":"Hydrogen.Schema.Color.CVD","reExports":[]}